&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Marches Medical Practice is looking for a Practice Nurse&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Marches Medical Practice is looking for a enthusiastic nurse  to work within our friendly team. Ideally, we are looking for someone with experience of Primary Care, who may have just completed their GPN course or relatively new to General Practice. We see the role as a development role increasing knowledge and skills starting in a junior role. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience of Primary Care is desirable but transferable skills may also be considered.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a friendly and well established training practice. 15,400 patients across two sites, Broughton and Buckley. We have 14 GPs, 1 ANP, 6 Nurses, 3 HCA’s and a clinical assistant. We train medical students and registrars.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post is 25-30 hours per week (Monday to Friday) between the hours of 8.30-18.30, days and sessions to be arranged.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Main duties of the job&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The following are the core responsibilities of the practice nurse to carry out competently without direct supervision following practice protocols;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Childhood immunisations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;General immunisations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cervical cytology&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Health promotion&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Chronic disease management- &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Health checks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Learning disability health checks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;.  &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please refer to the attached job description and person specification for full list of responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1.&lt;/strong&gt;     &lt;strong&gt;Qualifications &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Registered General Nurse Qualifications/Certificates in Chronic diseases, cervical smears desirable &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Recognised qualification to diploma level or above desirable &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A demonstrable commitment to professional development &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; 2. Experience &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience of working in accordance with the UKCC Code of Professional Conduct and The Scope of Professional Practice &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Computer literacy – experience of EMIS desirable &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience of dealing with the public/patients &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;3. Knowledge/Skills &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competent in basic nursing duties required for the post &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Specific nursing skills / qualifications desirable for a junior Practice Nurse role &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication skills &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;4. Qualities/Attributes &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to demonstrate enthusiasm to developing nursing skills &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An understanding, acceptance and adherence to the need for strict confidentiality Ability to use own judgement, resourcefulness and common sense &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work without direct supervision and determine own workload priorities Ability to work as part of an integrated multi-skilled team &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pleasant and articulate &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to work under pressure &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to work in a changing environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to use own initiative&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
